3)\n*  1935   &ndash; [[Peter Hollingworth]], Australian bishop, 23rd [[Governor General of Australia]]\n*[[1936]] &ndash; [[John Howell (athlete)|John Howell]], English long jumper\n*  1936   &ndash; [[John Madden]], American football player, coach, and sportscaster\n*  1936   &ndash; [[Bobby Smith (rhythm and blues singer)|Bobbie Smith]], American singer (d. 2013)\n*[[1937]] &ndash; [[Bella Akhmadulina]], Soviet and Russian poet, short story writer, and translator (d. 2010)\n*[[1938]] &ndash; [[Don Meredith]], American football player and sportscaster (d. 2010)\n*[[1939]] &ndash; [[Claudio Magris]], Italian scholar, author, and translator\n*[[1940]] &ndash; [[Gloria Hunniford]], British radio and television host\n*[[1941]] &ndash; [[Harold Long]], Canadian politician (d. 2013)\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Paul Theroux]], American novelist, short story writer, and travel writer\n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Nick Auf der Maur]], Canadian journalist and politician (d. 1998)\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Ian Callaghan]], English footballer\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Stuart Dybek]],  American novelist, short story writer, and poet\n*[[1943]] &ndash; [[Andrzej Bade\u0144ski]], Polish-German sprinter (d. 2008)\n*  1943   &ndash; [[Margaret Pemberton]], English author\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Kevin Berry]], Australian swimmer (d. 2006)\n*[[1946]] &ndash; [[David Angell]], American screenwriter and producer (d. 2001)\n*  1946   &ndash; [[Bob Watson]], American baseball player and manager\n*  1946   &ndash; [[Adolf Winkelmann (film director)|Adolf Winkelmann]], German director, producer, and screenwriter\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[David A. Adler]], American author and educator\n*  1947   &ndash; [[Bunny Wailer]], Jamaican singer-songwriter and drummer \n*[[1948]] &ndash; [[Mel Blount]], American football player\n*[[1949]] &ndash; [[Daniel Mangeas]], French banker and sportscaster\n*[[1949]] &ndash; [[Eric Troyer]], American singer-songwriter, keyboardist and guitarist\n*[[1950]] &ndash; [[Ken Griffey, Sr.]], American baseball player and manager\n*  1950   &ndash; [[Eddie Hazel]], American guitarist (d. 1992)\n*[[1951]] &ndash; [[David Helvarg]], American journalist and activist\n*[[1952]] &ndash; [[Narayan Rane]], Indian politician, 16th [[Chief Minister of Maharashtra]]\n*  1952   &ndash; [[Masashi Sada]], Japanese singer, lyricist, composer, novelist, actor, and producer\n*  1952   &ndash; [[Steven Seagal]], American actor, producer, and martial artist\n*[[1953]] &ndash; [[David Moorcroft]], English runner and businessman\n*  1953   &ndash; [[Pamela Wallin]], Swedish-Canadian journalist, academic, and politician\n*[[1954]] &ndash; [[Paul Bearer]], American wrestler and manager (d. 2013)\n*  1954   &ndash; [[Anne Lamott]], American author and educator\n*  1954   &ndash; [[Peter MacNicol]], American actor\n*  1954   &ndash; [[Juan Williams]], Panamanian-American journalist and author\n*[[1955]] &ndash; [[Lesley Garrett]], English soprano and actress\n*[[1956]] &ndash; [[Carol V. Robinson]], English chemist and academic\n*[[1957]] &ndash; [[Aliko Dangote]], Nigerian businessman, founded [[Dangote Group]]\n*  1957   &ndash; [[John M. Ford]], American author and poet (d. 2006)\n*  1957   &ndash; [[Steve Gustafson]], Spanish-American bass player \n*  1957   &ndash; [[Rosemary Hill]], English historian and author\n*[[1958]] &ndash; [[Bob Bell (motorsport)|Bob Bell]], Northern Irish engineer\n*  1958   &ndash; [[Yefim Bronfman]], Uzbek-American pianist\n*  1958   &ndash; [[Brigitte Holzapfel]], German high jumper\n*[[1959]] &ndash; [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]], American singer-songwriter and producer \n*  1959   &ndash; [[Yvan Loubier]], Canadian economist and politician\n*  1959   &ndash; [[Brian Setzer]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist\n*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Steve Bisciotti]], American businessman, co-founded [[Allegis Group]]\n*  1960   &ndash; [[Katrina Leskanich]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*  1960   &ndash; [[Terry Teagle]], American basketball player\n*[[1961]] &ndash; [[Nicky Campbell]], Scottish broadcaster and journalist\n*  1961   &ndash; [[Joe Cole (roadie)|Joe Cole]], American roadie and author (d. 1991)\n*  1961   &ndash; [[Carole Goble]], English computer scientist and academic\n*  1961   &ndash; [[Mark Jones (basketball, born 1961)|Mark Jones]], American basketball player\n*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Steve Tasker]], American football player and sportscaster\n*[[1963]] &ndash; [[Warren DeMartini]], American guitarist and songwriter \n*  1963   &ndash; [[Jeff Gray (baseball, born 1963)|Jeff Gray]], American baseball player and coach\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Doris Leuthard]], Swiss lawyer and politician, 162nd [[List of Presidents of the Swiss Confederation|President of the Swiss Confederation]]\n*[[1965]] &ndash; [[Tim Alexander]], American drummer and songwriter \n*[[1966]] &ndash; [[Steve Claridge]], English footballer, manager, and sportscaster\n*[[1967]] &ndash; [[Donald Dufresne]], Canadian ice hockey player and coach\n*  1967   &ndash; [[David Rovics]], American singer-songwriter\n*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Metin G\u00f6ktepe]], Turkish photographer and journalist (d. 1996)\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Orlando Jones]], American actor, producer, and screenwriter\n*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Steve Glasson]], Australian lawn bowler\n*  1969   &ndash; [[Ekaterini Koffa]], Greek sprinter\n*[[1970]] &ndash; [[Enrico Ciccone]], Canadian ice hockey player\n*  1970   &ndash; [[Leonard Doroftei]], Romanian-Canadian boxer\n*  1970   &ndash; [[Kenny Lattimore]], American singer-songwriter\n*  1970   &ndash; [[Q-Tip (musician)|Q-Tip]], American rapper, producer, and actor \n*[[1971]] &ndash; [[Brad William Henke]], American football player and actor\n*  1971   &ndash; [[Indro Olumets]], Estonian footballer and coach\n*  1971   &ndash; [[Al Reyes]], Dominican-American baseball player\n*[[1972]] &ndash; [[Ian Harvey]], Australian cricketer\n*  1972   &ndash; [[Priit Kasesalu]], Estonian computer programmer, co-created [[Skype]]\n*  1972   &nda