ing Oliver]], American cornet player and bandleader (b. 1885)\n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Carl Schenstr\u00f8m]], Danish actor and director (b. 1881)\n*[[1943]] &ndash; [[Andreas Faehlmann]], Estonian-German sailor and engineer (b. 1898)\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Hendrik Nicolaas Werkman]], Dutch printer and typographer (b. 1882)\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Charles Nordhoff]], English-American lieutenant and author (b. 1887)\n*[[1950]] &ndash; [[Fevzi \u00c7akmak]], Turkish field marshal and politician, 2nd [[List of Prime Ministers of Turkey|Prime Minister of Turkey]] (b. 1876)\n*[[1954]] &ndash; [[Auguste and Louis Lumi\u00e8re|Auguste Lumi\u00e8re]], French director and producer (b. 1862)\n*  1954   &ndash; [[Oscar Mathisen]], Norwegian speed skater (b. 1888)\n*[[1955]] &ndash; [[Pierre Teilhard de Chardin]], French priest, theologian, and philosopher (b. 1881)\n*[[1958]] &ndash; [[Chuck Willis]], American singer-songwriter (b. 1928)\n*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Andr\u00e9 Berthomieu]], French director and screenwriter (b. 1903)\n*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Michael Curtiz]], Hungarian-American director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1886)\n*  1962   &ndash; [[Stuart Sutcliffe]], Scottish artist and musician (b. 1940)\n*[[1965]] &ndash; [[Lloyd Casner]], American race car driver, founded [[Casner Motor Racing Division]] (b. 1928)\n*  1965   &ndash; [[Linda Darnell]], American actress (b. 1923)\n*[[1966]] &ndash; [[Evelyn Waugh]], English soldier, novelist, journalist and critic (b. 1903)\n*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Gustavs Celmi\u0146\u0161]], Latvian lieutenant and politician (b. 1899)\n*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Harley Earl]], American businessman (b. 1893)\n*[[1975]] &ndash; [[Walker Evans]], American photographer (b. 1903)\n*  1975   &ndash; [[Marjorie Main]], American actress (b. 1890)\n*[[1978]] &ndash; [[Hjalmar M\u00e4e]], Estonian politician (b. 1901)\n*[[1979]] &ndash; [[Nino Rota]], Italian pianist, composer, and conductor (b. 1911)<ref>{{cite book|author1=F. Maurice Speed|author2=Speed|title=Film Review: 1979-1980|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jeia-Mi28JwC|date=1 November 1979|publisher=Penguin Group (USA) Incorporated|isbn=978-0-8015-2632-9|page=168}}</ref>\n*[[1980]] &ndash; [[Kay Medford]], American actress and singer (b. 1919)\n*[[1981]] &ndash; [[Howard Thurman]], American author, philosopher and civil rights activist (b. 1899)\n*[[1983]] &ndash; [[Issam Sartawi]], Palestinian activist (b. 1935)\n*[[1985]] &ndash; [[Zisis Verros]], Greek chieftain of the Macedonian Struggle (b. 1880)\n*[[1986]] &ndash; [[Linda Creed]], American singer-songwriter (b. 1948)\n*[[1991]] &ndash; [[Kevin Peter Hall]], American actor (b. 1955)\n*  1991   &ndash; [[Martin Hannett]], English guitarist and producer (b. 1948)\n*  1991   &ndash; [[Natalie Schafer]], American actress (b. 1900)\n*[[1992]] &ndash; [[Sam Kinison]], American comedian and actor (b. 1953)\n*[[1993]] &ndash; [[Chris Hani]], South African activist and politician (b. 1942)\n*[[1994]] &ndash; [[Sam B. Hall, Jr.]], American lawyer, judge, and politician (b. 1924)\n*[[1995]] &ndash; [[Morarji Desai]], Indian politician, 4th [[Prime Minister of India]] (b. 1896)\n*[[1997]] &ndash; [[Michael Dorris]], American author and academic (b. 1945)\n*  1998   &ndash; [[Seraphim of Athens]], Greek archbishop (b. 1913)\n*[[1999]] &ndash; [[Heinz Fraenkel-Conrat]], German-American biochemist and physician (b. 1910)\n*  1999   &ndash; [[Jean Vander Pyl]], American actress and voice artist (b. 1919)\n*[[2000]] &ndash; [[Peter Jones (actor)|Peter Jones]], English actor and screenwriter (b. 1920)\n*  2000   &ndash; [[Larry Linville]], American actor (b. 1939)<ref>{{cite news |title='M*A*S*H' actor Linville dead at 60 |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2000/SHOWBIZ/TV/04/11/larry.linville/ |work=[[CNN]] |date=April 11, 2000 |access-date=April 21, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[2003]] &ndash; [[Little Eva]], American singer (b. 1943)\n*[[2004]] &ndash; [[Jacek Kaczmarski]], Polish singer-songwriter, guitarist, and poet (b. 1957)\n*  2004   &ndas